                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="19053" author="juergen.hoeller" created="Mon, 14 Aug 2006 12:05:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Well, the problem is that we cannot check the ServletContext implementation class upfront, since we don&apos;t have access to it - we can just check the ServletContext interface, which will always expose the &quot;getExpressionEvaluator()&quot; method with such a hacked JSP API on the classpath. What we can do, though, is to catch the NoSuchMethodError on first access and try to adapt accordingly.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Juergen&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="19055" author="tommack" created="Mon, 14 Aug 2006 15:28:22 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I guess my first impression was to delay setting the helper variable until first access. Then the actual class of the pageContext variable can be inspected.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="19313" author="juergen.hoeller" created="Wed, 30 Aug 2006 09:25:30 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve added a fallback to Jsp20ExpressionEvaluationHelper: It uses a JakartaExpressionEvaluationHelper as fallback if possible. So the startup detection will still lead to Jsp20ExpressionEvaluationHelper being chosen, but if a NoSuchMethodError gets thrown on first access, it immediately switches the fallback on (which has been initialized at startup as well). So the synchronization effort is minimal - essentially just a boolean flag.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Juergen&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="20187" author="pmularien" created="Tue, 10 Oct 2006 23:34:59 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;For reference, discussion about this bug also occurring in Spring 1.2.x is in &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.spring.io/browse/SPR-2628&quot; title=&quot;ClassCastException within Commons EL when called from spring:message tag&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SPR-2628&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SPR-2628&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
